# Website Traffic Analysis using Python

## Project Overview

This project analyzes website traffic data to understand user behavior, engagement metrics, traffic patterns, bounce rates, and conversion performance.

The project helps businesses improve:
- Website performance
- User engagement
- Customer retention
- Marketing effectiveness
- Conversion optimization

---

## Objectives

The main objectives of this project are:

- Analyze website visitor behavior
- Understand traffic source performance
- Measure user engagement
- Evaluate bounce rates
- Analyze conversion performance
- Generate business insights and recommendations

---

## Tools & Technologies Used

- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Jupyter Notebook

---

## Dataset Features

The dataset contains the following columns:

- Page Views
- Session Duration
- Bounce Rate
- Traffic Source
- Time on Page
- Previous Visits
- Conversion Rate

---

## Project Workflow

1. Data Collection
2. Data Cleaning
3. Missing Value Analysis
4. Duplicate Value Analysis
5. Statistical Summary
6. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
7. Data Visualization
8. Correlation Analysis
9. KPI Reporting
10. Feature Engineering
11. Business Insights
12. Business Recommendations

---

## Exploratory Data Analysis Performed

The following analyses were performed:

- Traffic Source Analysis
- Page Views Distribution
- Session Duration Analysis
- Bounce Rate Analysis
- Time on Page Analysis
- Previous Visits Analysis
- Conversion Rate Analysis
- Correlation Heatmap
- Pairplot Visualization
- Engagement Score Analysis

---

## Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)

The following KPIs were analyzed:

- Total Page Views
- Average Session Duration
- Average Bounce Rate
- Average Conversion Rate
- Returning Visitors Count

---

## Key Insights

- Organic traffic generated the highest engagement.
- Users with longer session durations showed higher conversion behavior.
- Returning visitors contributed significantly to website engagement.
- Higher bounce rates negatively affected conversion performance.
- Most users viewed between 3–6 pages during sessions.

---

## Feature Engineering

A new metric called **Engagement Score** was created using:
- Page Views
- Session Duration
- Bounce Rate

This helped identify highly engaged users.

---

## Business Recommendations

- Improve pages with high bounce rates.
- Focus more on high-performing traffic sources.
- Improve customer retention strategies.
- Optimize low-performing pages.
- Enhance website user experience and content quality.

---

